SUMMARY: The current and former senators and former national security adviser were among 21 people who ultimately were not charged in the election interference case

SUMMARY: A group affiliated with Senate Republicans said this week that the term "pro-life" is no longer resonating with voters

TITLE: Vivek Ramaswamy says he'll deport children of undocumented immigrants born in the U.S.
SUMMARY: Those children, however, are American citizens under the 14th Amendment

SUMMARY: Eric Munchel and his mother, Lisa Marie Eisenhart, were captured in photos and videos during the Capitol riot carrying plastic zip tie-style handcuffs

SUMMARY: The appeal by the Biden administration could lead to a final decision in the contentious legal fight over the FDA's approval of mifepristone

TITLE: Mississippi Democrat set to become state's first openly gay lawmaker after primary win
SUMMARY: “I still think I’m in a dream. I’m still trying to process it and take it in,” Fabian Nelson said after his historic victory
